abstract = {For many people, the habit of leg shaking is an annoyance to themselves and people around them. By simply becoming aware of the motion, one is able to voluntarily stop shaking. In this work, we present SPINDLES, a low-power, low-latency, non-intrusive and high accuracy mobile application to detect leg shaking and notify the user in a timely manner. SPINDLES is robust to the placement of the phone and implements a signal processing pipeline that eliminates the need for training and calibration phases common in machine learning approaches. We compare SPINDLES with other detection algorithms and existing Google Play Store applications, and find that SPINDLES is a major improvement in terms of accuracy with comparable latency and power consumption. It has a true positive rate of 99.6%, as well as a true negative rate of 97.6%, taken over 500 trials in various situations1.},
